k\">{{cite web |url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/death-from-above-outrage-is-now/|title=Death from Above \u2013 Outrage! Is Now |publisher=[[Pitchfork Media]] |date=September 11, 2014 |accessdate=September 11, 2017 |first=Saby |last=Reyes-Kulkarni}}</ref>\n| noprose = yes\n}}\n\n'''''Outrage! Is Now''''' is the third studio album by Canadian [[Rock music|rock]] duo [[Death from Above (band)|Death from Above]].  It was released on September 8, 2017, through [[Last Gang Records]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.spin.com/2017/08/death-from-above-new-album-outrage-is-now/|title=Death From Above Announce New Album Outrage! Is Now, Release \"Never Swim Alone\" Video|work=[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]|last=Josephs|first=Brian|date=August 15, 2017|accessdate=August 25, 2017}}</ref> The album was produced by [[Eric Valentine]] who has previously worked with artists such as [[Queens of the Stone Age]], [[Smash Mouth]], [[Third Eye Blind]] and [[Good Charlotte]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.hmv.com/music/death-from-above-outrage-is-now-interview|title=Death From Above talk hmv.com through the making of their new album Outrage! Is Now|website=HMV|language=en-GB|access-date=2017-10-27}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n|title1   = Nomad\n|length1  = 4:10\n|title2   = Freeze Me\n|length2  = 3:18\n|title3   = Caught Up\n|length3  = 4:30\n|title4   = Outrage! Is Now\n|length4  = 3:32\n|title5   = Never Swim Alone\n|length5  = 2:34\n|title6   = Moonlight\n|length6  = 3:10\n|title7   = Statues\n|length7  = 4:36\n|title8   = All I C Is U & Me\n|length8  = 3:00\n|title9   = Nvr 4evr\n|length9  = 3:50\n|title10  = Holy Books\n|length10 = 3:49\n|total_length = 36:29\n}}\n\n==Personnel==\n'''Death from Above'''\n*[[Jesse F. Keeler]] \u2013 bass guitar, synthesizer, keyboards, backing vocals\n*[[Sebastien Grainger]] \u2013 lead vocals, backing vocals, drums, percussion\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\